3. Normative Data Test developers administer the test to a sample of hundreds or thousands of participants drawn from the target population. Normative scores and percentiles are derived from these individuals. 
NCBI

For BariAccess: Your 466-patient cohort is exactly this. A psychometrician runs your cohort data and establishes what scores are normal, what scores indicate drift, and whether your band thresholds are clinically meaningful.

