QUESTION 2 — WHAT DOES FAB FREQUENCY MEAN?
FAB frequency means how often the patient completes their FAB per week. In the canonical architecture FABs have three operating levels — Standby, Wedge, and Program. Frequency is one component of the FACTS methodology — the F in FACTS.

For scoring purposes:

High frequency:   5-7 completions per week → V2 = 85-95
Normal frequency: 3-4 completions per week → V2 = 70-84
Low frequency:    1-2 completions per week → V2 = 50-69
Zero:             0 completions            → V2 = 20-40
